stats_extension_index.description: Censor cells of a pivot table based on the values of a tests

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC CENSOR TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Censor cells of a pivot table based on the values of a test statistic
extension_detail_info.Description: Use this command to blank out or otherwise obscure cells in the most recent pivot table of a selected type based on the value of a specified statistic in the table. For example, you can blank out cell statistics based on small counts or blank out insignificant correlations in a correlation matrix.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Compare two open datasets.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC COMPARE DATASETS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compare two open datasets.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure compares two open datasets. You can specify whether the comparison includes the case data, the variable properties or both.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Create a set of dummy variables representing the values of on

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC CREATE DUMMIES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a set of dummy variables representing the values of one or more variables and interaction terms
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure creates a set of 0-1 dummy variables representing the distinct values of one or more variables. It can also create dummies for two- and three-way interaction terms.  It is useful, for example, in converting categorical variables into a set of variables appropriate for use in the Regression procedure. It can optionally create  macro variables representing sets of dummies.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Open an SPSS, Excel, SAS, or Stata dataset from a web url.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC GETURI DATA
extension_detail_info.Summary: Open an SPSS, Excel, SAS, or Stata dataset from a web url.
extension_detail_info.Description: This command takes a URL as input and downloads and opens a data file.  It can be used to download and save files of other types, but these will not be opened.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Calculate correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale va

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC HETCOR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale variables.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates correlations between nominal, ordinal, and scale variables, accounting for the measurement levels of the variables. The resulting heterogeneous correlation matrix consists of Pearson product-moment correlations between scale variables, polyserial correlations between scale and categorical variables, and polychoric correlations between categorical variables. The procedure uses the hetcor function from the R polycor package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Merge the contents of one pivot table in the Viewer into anot

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MERGE TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Merge the contents of one pivot table in the Viewer into another.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure combines cell values from one table with values in another table. The most common usage is to combine proportion or means test tables from Custom Tables with the main table, but many other kinds of merges are possible.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Modify the appearance of pivot tables.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MODIFY TABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Modify the appearance of pivot tables.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure allows you to modify the appearance of data cells and row and column labels. You can modify text style, text color or background color. You can also set column widths or the width of row labels and you can hide specified rows or columns.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Apply a file of syntax to a set of data files

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROCESS FILES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Apply a file of syntax to a set of data files
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure applies a file of syntax to each of a group of selected files. It defines file handles and macros for use in the syntax file, and provides various options for handling Viewer and data output.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate a regression with fractional polynomials for the scale variables

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MFP GLM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a regression with fractional polynomials for the scale variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates fractional polynomial models with a variety of link functions.  Controls are available to limit the degree of the polynomial
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Modify output titles and other aspects of objects in the View

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC MODIFY OUTPUT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Modify output titles and other aspects of objects in the Viewer
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure allows you to modify the text of specified items in the outline pane of the Viewer as well as the titles (such as pivot table titles) or text (such as for title items) of the associated items. Replacement text can contain html or rtf formatting notation. Optionally, you can hide specified items and you can insert page breaks before specified title items.  Using included custom functions, selected items can be exported, and there is extra page break functionality.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Search the cases in a set of SPSS SAV files

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROCESS FILES_SEARCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: Search the cases in a set of SPSS SAV files
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure provides a way to search through the cases in a collection of similarly structured data files and display information from those matching the search criteria. You specify the files to search, the case selection criterion, and the variables to display for the selected cases. This bundle requires the SPSSINC PROCESS FILES extension.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Extension command to run arbitrary Python programs without tu

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC PROGRAM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Extension command to run arbitrary Python programs without turning them into extension commands
extension_detail_info.Description: This extension command allows you to run Python programs as if they were extension commands but without actually making them into such.  The primary benefit is that it is easy to pass parameters to programs this way.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Two variable or two group Q-Q plot

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC QQPLOT2
extension_detail_info.Summary: Two variable or two group Q-Q plot
extension_detail_info.Description: The standard Q-Q plot in Statistics plots a variable against a theoretical distribution.  This package produces a Q-Q plot of one variable against another one or a plot of a variable's distribution in one group against the distribution in another group.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate one or more conditional quantiles for a linear model.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC QUANTREG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate one or more conditional quantiles for a linear model.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates one or more conditional quantiles (0 <= q <= 1) for a linear model, using the rq function from the R quantreg package. In contrast, ordinary regression estimates the conditional mean. The procedure allows you to choose the estimation algorithm as well as the method for estimating the standard error. You can save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Calculate weights to control totals in up to ten dimensions by rim weighting, i.e. raking

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC_RAKE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate weights to control totals in up to ten dimensions by rim weighting, i.e. raking
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates a weight so that the case count will match specified control totals in one to ten dimensions.  This procedure requires the Advanced Statistics option.  Version 2.4 improves the weight calculations when there is an input weight.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate random forest

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RANFOR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate random forest
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure builds random forests of classification or regression trees.  It also supports unsupervised mode, in which case proximities are calculated.  The companion procedure SPSSINC RANPRED calculates predictions for new data using the forest built by this procedure.  Note: this version is a major rewrite of the older SPSSINC RANFOR procedure and  no longer requires the Python plugin.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Compute predicted values for new data using forests from SPSS

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RANPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute predicted values for new data using forests from SPSSINC RANFOR
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure uses a forest produced by the SPSSINC RANFOR extension command to compute predicted values for new data.  It is a complete rewrite of the older extension command and no longer requires the Python plugin.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate a Rasch model for item response data.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC RASCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a Rasch model for item response data.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates the parameters of the Rasch model for item response data, using the rasch function from the R ltm package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate a linear regression model by robust regression, using an M estimator

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC ROBUST REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a linear regression model by robust regression, using an M estimator.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a linear regression model, robustly, using an M estimator. It uses the rlm function from the R MASS package. The procedure allows you to save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Define a macro listing variables selected according to variable dictionary properties

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC SELECT VARIABLES
extension_detail_info.Summary: Define a macro listing variables selected according to variable dictionary properties
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides a way to select variables based on a combination of criteria.  The criteria can include names, patterns in the names, variable type, measurement level, role, and custom attributes.  Using this method, jobs can be generalized so that they do not require hard-wired variable names.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate a linear model and perform a heteroscedasticity test.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC BREUSCH PAGAN
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a linear model and perform a heteroscedasticity test.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a linear model and performs the Breusch-Pagan heteroscedasticity test, using the ncv.test function from the R car package. The null hypothesis is constant error variance. You can specify whether the alternative is that the variance is a function of the dependent variable or a function of a specified set of predictors. The procedure allows you to save both the residuals from the regression and the estimated coefficients.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Split a dataset into separate files according to splitting va

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC SPLIT DATASET
extension_detail_info.Summary: Split a dataset into separate files according to splitting variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure partitions a dataset into a set of sav files according to the values of one or more splitting variables.  Used with SPSSINC PROCESS FILES, it provides a generalization of the built-in SPLIT FILES mechanism.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate a regression model whose dependent variable has a fi

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TOBIT REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate a regression model whose dependent variable has a fixed lower bound, upper bound, or both.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a regression model where the dependent variable has a fixed lower bound, upper bound, or both. It can be thought of as a combination of a probit model with a linear regression model. You can specify the distribution assumed for the dependent variable, and you can save the residuals from the regression as well as the estimated coefficients. The procedure uses the tobit function from the R AER package.
extension_detail_info.Author: IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Apply a Python function to case data.

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TRANS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Apply a Python function to case data.
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure applies a Python function to the cases in the active dataset and saves the results to one or more new or existing variables. This allows you to apply Python functions to your case data, much like you do with built-in functions such as those available with the COMPUTE command.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Framework for translating Viewer output

extension_detail_info.Name: SPSSINC TRANSLATE OUTPUT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Framework for translating Viewer output
extension_detail_info.Description: This package provides a mechanism for translating Viewer output based on a set of supplementary files containing translations.  See the included file translator.doc for instructions.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Adjust widths of string variables across files

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS ADJUST WIDTHS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Adjust widths of string variables across files
extension_detail_info.Description: This command synchronizes the widths of selected string variables across a set of files or datasets. This is mainly useful when combining files with MATCH  or ADD.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM

stats_extension_index.description: Calculate canonical correlations

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CANCORR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate canonical correlations
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedures computes canonical correlations for two sets of variables.  It can create scores, and it can produce a syntax file that can be used to score other datasets with the same variable names.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Compute the Cartesian product of two sets of variables

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CARTPROD
extension_detail_info.Summary: Compute the Cartesian product of two sets of variables
extension_detail_info.Description: This command takes two sets of variables either from the active dataset or the active dataset plus one other dataset and creates a new data file containing the Cartesian product of the variables.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Create a macro or multiple dichotomy set with a specified var

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CATEGORY ORDER
extension_detail_info.Summary: Create a macro or multiple dichotomy set with a specified variable order
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure takes a list of ordinary variables or multiple dichotomy sets.  For ordinary variables, it creates a macro listing the variables in sorted order of the count.  This macro can be used in the CTABLES CATEGORIES subcommand to control the order in the table.  Unlike CTABLES, it can move special values out of the sort order.  For multiple dichotomy sets, it creates a new set with the categories similarly reordered.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: compute silhouette measure for cluster analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS CLUS SIL
extension_detail_info.Summary: compute silhouette measure for cluster analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure computes and optionally plots silhouette measures useful in assessing the quality of a cluster analysis.  It provides several different dissimilarity measures and plots that work with the output from a cluster analysis procedure
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Competing risk survival regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS COMPRISK
extension_detail_info.Summary: Competing risk survival regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates the   competing risks survival regression model.  This model allows for multiple   competing causes for the failure event.  These could, for example, be multiple   health conditions or multiple part failures in a mechanical or electrical device.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Cox (proportional hazards) regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS COXREGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Cox (proportional hazards) regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates Cox regession.  It has some features not available in the Statistics COXREG procedure.  It supports left and/or right censoring via a counting process model.  Time dependent variables are supported via either a formula or multiple observations per subject.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Define date structure based on dataset values

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DATA_DATE
extension_detail_info.Summary: Define date structure based on dataset values
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure defines the date structure of the dataset based on the first value of an SPSS date variable
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Combine several DATASET commands into one

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DATASET
extension_detail_info.Summary: Combine several DATASET commands into one
extension_detail_info.Description: This command combines the functions of DATASET NAME, DATASET ACTIVATE, DATASET CLOSE, and DATASET DISPLAY into a single command.  It also allow you to close all the datasets except for a specified list without having to list every dataset individually.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Prediction based on density-based clustering

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DBPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Prediction based on density-based clustering
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure uses the results of the companion procedure, STATS_DBSCAN, to predict cluster values for new cases.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Density-based clustering

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_DBSCAN
extension_detail_info.Summary: Density-based clustering
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates density-based clusters allowing for noise.  The companion procedure, STATS_DBPRED, can be used to predict values for new cases.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Disaggregate a time series into a series at a higher frequency

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DISAGG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Disaggregate a time series into a series at a higher frequency
extension_detail_info.Description: This command creates a new dataset containing a time series at a higher frequency than the original.  It can use higher frequency indicator variables with which the low frequency is correlated to distribute the values or distribute less accurately without such indicators.  Several methods are supported.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Fit probability distributions

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS DISTFIT
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit probability distributions
extension_detail_info.Description: This package fits one or more selected probability distributions to a collection of variables.  The output includes the fit parameters, a goodness-of-fit test, and, optionally, Q-Q plots.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate system of linear equations

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS EQNSYSTEM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate system of linear equations
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure estimates a system of linear equations by 3SLS, 2SLS, SUR, or OLS.  The dialog box handles only two equations, but an unlimited number can be used in syntax.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Firth logistic regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS FIRTHLOG
extension_detail_info.Summary: Firth logistic regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates the Firth logistic regression model, which can address the separation issues that can arise in standard logistic regression.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: GARCH models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GARCH
extension_detail_info.Summary: GARCH models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates a variety of univariate GARCH models.  The models can be used for forecasting.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate generalized boosted regression models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate generalized boosted regression models
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure produces a set (ensemble) of individually weak regression models that in the aggregate can predict a dependent variable more accurately than standard models.  It covers distributions from gaussian to Bernoulli -a total of ten distributions.  It is based on the R gbm package which follows the Friedman gradient boosting method.  This package performs the estimation.  The accompanying package, STATS GBMPRED, is used to calculate predictions based on the results of this procedure.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM

stats_extension_index.description: Calculate predictions from generalized boosted regression mod

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS GBMPRED
extension_detail_info.Summary: Calculate predictions from generalized boosted regression models created with STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Description: This package is a companion to the STATS GBM package, which creates generalized boosted regression models.  The package reads the results of STATS GBM and creates a new dataset of predictions for new data.  It is based on the R gbm package also used by STATS GBM
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Fit graded response models to ordinal data

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_GRM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit graded response models to ordinal data
extension_detail_info.Description: Fits the grm function from the R ltm package to graded response data
extension_detail_info.Author: Alex Reutter, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Estimate censored/truncated regression or switching regression

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_HECKMAN_REGR
extension_detail_info.Summary: Estimate censored/truncated regression or switching regression
extension_detail_info.Description: This package estimates Heckman two-step regression models for a censored or truncated dependent variable.  It can also estimate switching regressions. Estimation methods include maximum likelihood and two step.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Various inequality measures for a variable distribution

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS INEQUALITY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Various inequality measures for a variable distribution
extension_detail_info.Description: This command computes up to seven inequality measures, including the Gini coefficient, for a variable.  Confidence intervals are available for Gini coefficients.  Split files are supported, making group comparisons easy.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Fit three parameter item response models

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_IRM
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit three parameter item response models
extension_detail_info.Description: Executes the tpm function from the R ltm package.  The variable list specifies the items.  It is assumed that the values of these variables is 0,1.
extension_detail_info.Author: Alex Reutter, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Fit kernel-smoothed distributions

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS KERNEL DENSITY
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit kernel-smoothed distributions
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure calculates kernel-smoothed densities.  It can save the densities as datasets and plot them.  The calculations are similar to the smooths available via GPL.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Latent Class Analysis

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS LATENT CLASS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Latent Class Analysis
extension_detail_info.Description: Extension command for latent class analysis including latent class regression using the R poLCA package by Drew Linzer and Jeffrey Lewis
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Fit a loess curve to a model

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS LOESS
extension_detail_info.Summary: Fit a loess curve to a model
extension_detail_info.Description: This procedure fits a loess curve to a model with one to four independent variables and creates a new dataset.  The dataset contains the predicted values for the estimation data or new data as well as the prediction input data.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Solve linear and integer programming problems

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS_LP
extension_detail_info.Summary: Solve linear and integer programming problems
extension_detail_info.Description: This package solves linear and integer programming problems and mixed problems.  Bounds can be imposed on the objective function variables.  It can even be used to solve systems of linear equations by using all equality constraints.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS

stats_extension_index.description: Construct optimal bins for categorical or continuous target

extension_detail_info.Name: STATS OPTBINEX
extension_detail_info.Summary: Construct optimal bins for categorical or continuous target
extension_detail_info.Description: This command uses the TREE CHAID algorithm on a categorical or continuous target to group categories or ranges of predictor values that have statistically indistinguishable effects on the target.  It can carry out the transformations and save that syntax for future use.  It also provides value labels for the new variables.  Predictor variables are analyzed one at a time.  The results are similar to those from OPTIMAL BINNING for continuous variables and ADP, but has the advantage of exposing the transformations and providing labels.  The command requires the Decision Trees option, because it uses the TREE procedure.
extension_detail_info.Author: JKP, IBM SPSS
